Why do countries try to protect there own companies from world market exposure? The reason why countries do this is to protect their country from a loss in revenue. If a country has a lot of money to spend, they will try to spend it on businesses that are from that country. The reason why this is done is because it is easier to get a return of investment from a business that is in the same country as the person who is investing. This is done because it is easier to control the market share the business is getting.
